    {
      "type": "draw",
      "text": "The estate is being administered under informal procedure by the Personal Representative under the Massachusetts Uniform Probate Code without supervision by the Court.  Inventory and accounts are not required to be filed with the Court, but interested parties are entitled to notice regarding the administration from the Personal Representative and can petition the Court in any matter relating to the estate, including distribution of assets and expenses of administration.  Interested parties are entitled to petition the Court to institute formal proceedings and to obtain orders terminating or restricting the powers of Personal Representatives appointed under informal procedure. A copy of the Petition and Will, if any, can be obtained from the Petitioner.",
      "x": "3.175mm",
      "y": "6.243mm",
      "parentPath": "form1.BodyPage1.S8",
      "name": "StaticText6",
      "w": "196.85mm",
      "h": "31.349mm"
    },
